    <h1>Design & Acoustics</h1>
    <p class="dek">Architectural and acoustical design for new and renovated cinema and AV spaces, from concept to construction documents.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="block">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p>Magna-Tech's design team handles the architectural and acoustical planning that has to happen before equipment goes in the room — theatrical design, sound insulation calculations, and sketch-level acoustic design for new cinemas, theaters, and other AV spaces. In practice these two disciplines are sold and delivered together: a room's shape, materials, and isolation determine what the sound system inside it can actually achieve, so we plan them as one engagement rather than two.</p>

    <h2 id="architectural-design">Architectural Design</h2>
    <p>Theatrical and cinema architectural design and sourcing for new builds and renovations — from concept and technology planning through the construction documents a contractor needs to build.</p>

    <h2 id="audio-consulting-acoustical-design">Audio Consulting & Acoustical Design</h2>
    <p>Acoustical design, including sound insulation calculations and sketch-level acoustic design, along with sound-system consulting for cinema halls, theaters, and other AV spaces.</p>

    <p>Example: MTE's architectural design and equipment package for the Fusion Superplex in Nassau, Bahamas — a 9-auditorium complex including IMAX and 4DX — covered the space planning and technology decisions from concept through installation. See the full <a href="/portfolio/">Portfolio</a> for more.</p>

    <h2>Common questions</h2>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do I need architectural design and acoustical consulting as separate engagements?</summary>
      <p>Not usually. Because a room's construction directly affects what the sound system can do, we typically scope and deliver both together as one engagement.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>At what stage should I bring in Magna-Tech for a new cinema or theater build?</summary>
      <p>As early as concept and site planning — technology and acoustic decisions made at that stage are far cheaper to implement than changes made after construction documents are finalized.</p>
    </details>

